<br>
<br>
It would take a few seconds for Ary's eyes to adjust to the darkness of Innoruks Realm.  It was starkly different then the desert of Southern Ro.  <br>
<br>
Krushh moved past Ary barking orders....<br>
<br>
&quot;Shield wall...here..,&quot; Krushh whispered in a guttural attempt at High Elvish.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Casters....here...,&quot; he pointed to the ground.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Ary sniffed the air, and caught the familiar stench of decay that filled the air in Innoruks plane.  He checked his place in the shield wall and planted his feet.  He was holding the To'eryr D' Yvierse- the Banner of the Elite.  He was to be the center of the Elven Host.  He was very proud to earn this right.  <br>
<br>
Looking down for a moment, he saw the blue and white favor tucked neatly into his belt.  Inside the small silk sash was a golden lock of hair.  For one quiet moment, His thoughts drifted to the lady who asked him to bear it.  The thought of her honor inspired him.  He was to fight for her honor, for the Honor of the Elite and for the Knights of the Koada Vie.    <br>
<br>
&quot;ALL PRAISE INNORUK, OUR LORD AND CREATOR!!&quot;, the noise echo'd from the harsh blackend stonework.  The sudden noise startled Ary from his day dream.  He set his jaw to the grim task at hand.  <br>
<br>
Wilwen ran into the room in a low crouch and stood before Krushh.<br>
<br>
&quot;Three Golems of Spite, M'lord.....I say again....Three dread Golems are headed our way...&quot; reported Wilwen.  Wilwen winked at Ary and dove into the lingering shadows. <br>
<br>
&quot;Tis time, you earned your Keep!!!&quot; Shouted Krushh<br>
<br>
&quot;Ainea Elthe Klitne,&quot; (Hate breeds Contempt) shouted Aryllyian......<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
