<br>
Among the Elven Host, bright swords flashed from scabbards and as the faithful made themselves ready for attack.  In the center, a tall Elven paladin raised the Banner of the Elite into the air and shouted a warcry.<br>
<br>
The Golems, however, cared not.  They were created to be immune to the dread of battle moved foreward with awe inspiring speed and weight and crashed into the Elven line.<br>
<br>
<br>
The wave of Golems broke over the Elven host like an angry wave against the shore.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#BA9F70><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/udebbaduilia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Debba Duilia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Raid Leader</span><br>  Posts: 507<br> <font color=#F5F5DC>(4/23/02 10:59:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/felvenelitefrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=62.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rally the Elven Host</span><hr size=1> Strong like the Sea Wall the Elven stood and held there ground, casting the golems back to the ocean from where they came. Many Blades flung and arrows shot, many wounds and scars came of this battle. Many sat and cleaned their blood stained weapons, and poured water from their canteens on each others wounds. The Clerics and the enchanters sat and meditated restore their mana in hopes to help them all succeed. The Mighty Elven host now awaits the scouts return with word of what else may be in store.  <p>Debba Duilia <BR>
